text: Alfred Krauss (2 February 1908 - 11 June 1957) was a French gymnast. He competed in four events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1908 births Category:1957 deaths Category:French male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of France Category:Gymnasts at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Haut-Rhin
